<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-1867] liveBroker list not updated on a cluster with no topics</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1867</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, when there is no topic in a cluster, the controller doesn&apos;t send any UpdateMetadataRequest to the broker when it starts up. As a result, the liveBroker list in metadataCache is empty. This means that we will return incorrect broker list in TopicMetatadataResponse.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
